Of coarse, everyone reverts when they want the see the explosions over and over and over again

TUBM did not open a new page

You did.

TUBM is a wormhole

No, but I live in one

TUBM knows what SLS 2: Electric Boogaloo looks like

Cant say that I do. I just wish theyd stop pushing the test launch back.

tubm knows what shinigami love.

082305102022

False, I don't even know what that is.

TUBM is sitting in school right now.

Edited May 10, 2022 by BekfastDerp13
don't*

Nope. Im sitting in my car in a drive thru waiting to get my breakfast tacos. 
@BekfastDerp13 ever read the manga or see the anime Death Note? The context for my tubm: "L do you know Shinigami love apples"

if you havent seen the anime you should. Its dark but well done.

tubm has seen the anime as well as the japanese live action version. 
085805102022

Nope. Im sitting in my car in a drive thru waiting to get my breakfast tacos. 
@BekfastDerp13 ever read the manga or see the anime Death Note? The context for my tubm: "L do you know Shinigami love apples"

if you havent seen the anime you should. Its dark but well done.

085805102022

Anime yes, live no

TUBM has been to Tanegashima

Nope.

TUBM has made a new page.

So many times it is not funny.

TUBM is sniffling with a cold.

Thankfully, nope.  Just allergies.

TUBM knows the mixed blessing that is working from home.

hahahahahah rampant procrastination insues.

TUBM enjoys soup.

Soup, yes. But it's not Souptime yet.

TUBM can fastforward to Souptime

nope 

TUBM has broke ksp in one way or another

Yep... lel

TUBM is going to vacation sometime

Spoiler

(I will for 2 weeks, so I'll be offline by that time starting Sunday. So I'll try to play forum games a lot right now )

Probably never again, so enjoy yours.

TUBM has landed a rocket on the KSC launchpad.

Yes. In early career game when the rocket is basically a flea under a pod under a chute.

TUBM has flown an airplane under the R&D bridge at supersonic/hypersonic speeds.

I have flown under both the bridge and the passageway in 1 flight at slow speeds, I have flown at both supersonic and hypersonic speeds, over 4000m/s under 50,000 metres. (check my badge   ) But I don't believe anyone could do both those things at the same time and survive.

TUBM has never used the Abort button.

False. I actually care about the safety of my kerbals, and have used the abort button a few times.

TUBM has at least one Lego brick in their house.

Edited May 14, 2022 by Kerb24

Correct.

TUBM preforms cruel interesting and sadistic informative experiments on thief kerbals

apparently it's quite an effective way to stop parts of your rocket randomly disappearing (in fllight)

TUBM plays ksp with more than 100 mods

I don't know. You will know if you copy this into a .CKAN file, I suppose.

I've seen a total of 57 "name"s in that "depends" node. Some of them are just configs/textures for a core mod, so I would say it's around or less than 50.
